reviewText: These are 2 great titles for a more than reasonable price. I tried (unsuccessfully) to get them from Netflix but got tired of waiting so I decided to check out just buying them. I'm glad I did!

Kindof like The Notebook in that aspect but a whole different type of movie other than not knowing what to expect.  I LOVE IT!

Sea of Love is a great movie! Great plot line, interesting character development. John Goodman, Al Pacino, and Ellen Barkin make this a movie not to be missed. Movie with lots of twists and turns, great characters, good editing. Well worth your time.

SCENT OF A WOMAN and SEA OF LOVE were both very good Al Pacino films. They are totally different films from each other and Pacino gives very good performances in each. Well, Al Pacino's performance in SCENT OF A WOMAN may be his best. To the point, each of these films have terrific finales and that may be why these two were chosen to pair.
GREAT movie...a must see
Good double feature

Does it get any better than TWO Al Pacino movies on one dvd? :)  Both are awesome movies - Scent of a Woman is fun and sad and everything in between.  Sea of Love is a thriller without all the gore and blood but keeps you on the edge of your seat.  Warning - very steamy sex scenes between Ellen Barkin and Al Pacino in this one but oth well worth watching.
Scent of a Woman is one of my favorite movies but my husband hadn't seen it. he ended up liking it too. Sea of Love was just a bonus for us

Such a beautiful movie set, and it's easily in my top ten. I'm reviewing more of Scent of a Woman than sea of Love at least until I watch that. Al Pacino puts on a performance of a lifetime and made a two and a half hour movie fly by. The famous tango scene is utterly remarkable and it has to be one of my favorite scenes ever as well. This movie left me in awe and I had to just take a few minutes after watching it to really come down from such an amazing experience.
